th of these are useful if you know what you&#8217;re doing, but since they are generally limited to only managing passwords on one computer, they can also be a pain in the butt if you also browse the web from your mobile phone or iPad, or have a second computer.</p>\n<p>Here at the Seed, we&#8217;re fond of LastPass, a handy password manager that can be installed on your Mac, PC, iPhone and iPad. Since it synchronizes each device to a central Password Vault, which can be accessed by one password, it&#8217;s a pre</p>\n<p>http://lifehacker.com/5042616/five-best-password-managers</p>\n<p>http://ca.lifehacker.com/5799036/the-best-password-utilities-that-dont-store-your-data-in-the-cloud</p>\n<h2>Keychain Access (Mac Only)</h2>\n<h2>Sxipper</h2>\n<p>https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/4865</p>\n<h2>1Password</h2>\n<h2>Keeper</h2>\n<p>http://www.callpod.com/products/keeper</p>\n<h2>RoboForm (Windows)</h2>\n<h2>KeePass Password Safe</h2>\n<p>http://keepass.info/</p>\n<h2>LastPass</h2>\n<p>LastPass is a free online password manager and Form Filler that makes your web browsing easier and more secure.</p>\n<p>LastPass supports Chrome, Firefox, Internet Explorer, and Safari for Mac as a browser extension (and Opera, Safari for Windows, Opera Mini and more via Bookmarklets).</p>\n<h2>Browser Password Managers</h2>\n<h3>Google Chrome</h3>\n<h3>Firefox</h3>\n<h3>Internet Explorer</h3>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"http://theseednetwork.com/blog/2011/10/04/password-management-review/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"