:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"WPTavern: Avoid Hardcoding Your Copyright Information\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://www.wptavern.com/?p=6059\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/PgTSNKe6iw8/avoid-hardcoding-your-copyright-information\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1163:\"<p>How many of you still update your themes footer every year to change the copyright date? Thanks to a small snippet of code, you can add this to your footer.php file which will negate the need to manually change the copyright information every year. The code snippet is php the_time(&#8216;Y&#8217;) An excellent primer for how to use this snippet within the footer.php file is explained <a href=\"http://lorelle.wordpress.com/2007/09/03/displaying-the-date-in-your-wordpress-theme/\">via Lorelle VanFossen</a>. </p>\n<p>Related posts:<ol>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.wptavern.com/incsub-llc-accused-of-copyright-infringement\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Incsub LLC Accused Of Copyright Infringement\">Incsub LLC Accused Of Copyright Infringement</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.wptavern.com/code-snippet-to-reduce-memory-usage\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Code Snippet To Reduce Memory Usage\">Code Snippet To Reduce Memory Usage</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.wptavern.com/copyright-and-the-gpl\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Copyright And The GPL\">Copyright And The GPL</a></li>\n</ol></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~4/PgTSNKe6iw8\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" 